-- Qtel Offers $2.3 Billion for Wataniya Shares, Al-Rai Says
-- B y   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2012-07-01T08:03:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-01/qtel-offers-2-3-billion-for-wataniya-shares-al-rai-says.html
Qatar Telecom QSC offered to pay
about 640 million dinars ($2.3 billion) to purchase shares it
doesn’t own in  Kuwait ’s National Mobile Telecommunications Co.,
 Al-Rai  newspaper reported today, citing unidentified people
familiar with the matter.  Qatar’s biggest phone company, which holds a 52.5 percent
in the Kuwaiti operator, also known as  Wataniya Telecom , offered
2.67 dinars a share, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dahlia Kholaif in Kuwait at 
 dkholaif@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  